This paper is about video object segmentation using deep learning techniques. The paper proposes a novel algorithm that requires no finetuning, auxiliary inputs or post-processing, and segments a variable number of objects in a single forward-pass. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also mentions unsupervised learning and meta-learning, which are common in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper deals with video datasets, which suggests that it may also belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Finally, the paper mentions the robustness of the algorithm, which suggests that it may also belong to the robotics (cs.RO) sub-category.
